The matrices $C_{\odot +}$ and $C_{+ \odot}$ respectively convert polarizations from linear to circular and from circular to linear. In \cite{smirnov2011a} these matrices are called $H$ (for {\em hybrid}); here we  call them $C$ (for {\em conversion}).



